All settings are configurable in real time and do not require a UI reload. A chat message confirms when Scrollkeeper is fully loaded and it is safe to open Scrollkeeper History after login.

[HR]

[SIZE="4"][B]Manual Donation Logging[/B][/SIZE]

To manually inject mailed donations into the history cache:

• Open the Guild Roster  
• Right-click a member's name  
• Select [B]Log Donation[/B]

You may specify:
• Donation type  
• Gold value  
• Optional notes  

This is useful for logging donations that were mailed while you were offline or before Scrollkeeper was installed.

[HR]

[SIZE="4"][B]Chat Buttons[/B][/SIZE]

Two buttons are added to the top-right corner of the chat window:

• Open all Scrollkeeper windows  
• Open Scrollkeeper Settings directly  

These provide quick access without navigating through the menu system or manually opening multiple windows.

[HR]

[SIZE="4"][B]Notebook Search[/B][/SIZE]

The Notebook search field:

• Is not case-sensitive  
• Searches both subject lines and note bodies  
• Returns all matches within the selected category  

This makes locating archived mail logs and notes fast and reliable.

[HR]

[SIZE="4"][B]Mass Mail Sender[/B][/SIZE]

The Mass Mail tool allows you to:

• Create reusable mail templates  
• Preview the message before sending  
• Preview recipient lists  
• Filter recipients by guild, rank, or Provision Member group  
• Automatically remove members after mailing (optional)

After sending:
• A log entry is created in Scrollkeeper Notebook  
• Failed recipients are recorded   

[HR]

[SIZE="4"][B]Task Reminder System[/B][/SIZE]

The Task system includes preset tasks and fully customizable entries.

• Tasks display only on the roster of their assigned guild  
• A countdown timer shows time remaining  
• Clicking the timer resets it  

Perfect for tracking recurring guild responsibilities.
